Mr. Cash.

02:51.171 --> 02:52.548
J.R.

02:54.550 --> 02:56.760
J.R., turn it off and get to sleep.

02:57.678 --> 03:00.430
Change it, J.R. Turn it off.

03:07.187 --> 03:08.981
Guess which Carter that is.

03:11.024 --> 03:13.402
- Anita?
- Nope. June.

03:13.610 --> 03:15.571
<i>That was 10-year-old June singing.</i>

03:15.779 --> 03:17.281
<i>What was the name</i>
<i>of that number?</i>

03:17.739 --> 03:18.782
<i>I was gonna sing...</i>

03:18.991 --> 03:21.994
Turn it off.
Do I have to come in there?

03:22.160 --> 03:23.704
<i>Now here's the cut...</i>

03:25.247 --> 03:26.582
Let's get to bed.

03:39.344 --> 03:41.054
It's hot.

03:42.139 --> 03:44.391
It's gonna be hotter tomorrow.

03:44.600 --> 03:48.270
Maybe Daddy will quit us early
and we can go fishing.

03:48.729 --> 03:51.481
We'll go fishing Saturday.

03:52.649 --> 03:55.527
Daddy needs a good day
from us tomorrow, J.R.

03:55.652 --> 03:57.738
I know.

04:00.657 --> 04:03.076
- Jack?
- Mm-hm?

04:06.205 --> 04:08.207
How come you're so good?

04:10.250 --> 04:12.127
I ain't.

04:14.213 --> 04:17.841
- You pick five times more than me.
- Well, I'm bigger than you are.

04:18.634 --> 04:21.470
You know every story in Scripture.

04:21.637 --> 04:24.640
Well, you know every song
in Mama's hymnal.

04:24.806 --> 04:26.600
Songs are easy.

04:26.850 --> 04:28.810
They ain't for me.

04:29.019 --> 04:32.231
There's more words in the Bible
<i>than in Heavenly Highway Hymns.</i>

04:32.940 --> 04:35.150
Look, J.R., if I'm gonna be
a preacher one day...

04:35.317 --> 04:37.361
...I gotta know the Bible
front to back.

04:37.528 --> 04:41.198
I mean, you can't help nobody
if you can't tell them the right story.

04:50.791 --> 04:53.210
They said by noon it's gonna be 104.

04:53.961 --> 04:57.172
Them radio stations say anything
to get them niggers off.

04:58.257 --> 05:01.593
Ray, why don't you let J.R.
Take the babies in?

05:01.802 --> 05:04.429
I told Rollins
we'd have a crop yesterday.

05:04.555 --> 05:07.307
What do I say when he pulls up here
and we're shy?

05:07.432 --> 05:09.268
You ready to unload that piano?

05:10.519 --> 05:13.021
We're not selling Daddy's piano.

05:14.231 --> 05:17.150
And I'm not the one in Bardstown
drinking every Saturday.

05:23.323 --> 05:29.413
<i>Am I a soldier of the cross</i>

05:29.580 --> 05:33.500
<i>A follower of the Lamb</i>

05:33.709 --> 05:39.131
<i>And shall I fear to own His cause</i>

05:46.763 --> 05:49.474
Eh, what's up, doc?

06:11.538 --> 06:13.081
Whoa.

06:22.132 --> 06:25.302
Hey, what did that...? That rooster
say when he was all blown up...

06:25.511 --> 06:28.931
...by TNT and picking his feathers up
outside that henhouse?

06:29.890 --> 06:34.061
"Fortunately, boy, I keep my feathers
numbered for just such an emergency."

07:09.930 --> 07:11.890
I got it. I got it.

07:16.728 --> 07:18.814
Can we go soon?

07:18.981 --> 07:22.234
Mr. Coles gave me a dollar
to cut the whole pile and not half.

07:23.443 --> 07:26.738
Go on ahead, J.R. Catch a fish.

07:32.828 --> 07:35.664
<i>Put a worm on a hook</i>

07:37.749 --> 07:40.544
<i>And drop it in a brook</i>

07:42.880 --> 07:45.340
<i>If things go right</i>

07:47.759 --> 07:50.220
<i>You'll fry some fish tonight</i>

08:09.448 --> 08:12.159
Where you been? Where you been?

08:14.161 --> 08:17.789
Throw that pole down. Get in the car.
In the car.

08:51.949 --> 08:53.992
You hear them, J. R?

08:55.202 --> 08:57.204
Do you hear them angels?

08:57.371 --> 09:00.082
I can hear them, Jack.

09:00.290 --> 09:02.543
They're so beautiful.

09:02.751 --> 09:04.795
They're beautiful.

09:05.587 --> 09:07.464
Jack?

09:07.631 --> 09:09.174
Do something.

09:11.260 --> 09:13.720
Do something.

10:19.912 --> 10:21.413
You know what that is, J. R?

10:21.830 --> 10:23.749
- You know what that is...?
- Stop it, Ray.

10:23.874 --> 10:25.042
Nothing.

10:34.801 --> 10:38.013
Nothing. That's what that is.

10:39.348 --> 10:40.682
That's what that's worth.

10:41.558 --> 10:42.684
And that's what you are.

10:42.851 --> 10:45.229
Leave him alone, Ray. He didn't do this.

10:45.354 --> 10:48.148
The devil did this.
He took the wrong son.

10:49.691 --> 10:52.569
Stop it, Ray.
He was my best. Now he's gone.

10:52.694 --> 10:54.363
Jack, please don't leave me alone.

10:54.530 --> 10:55.614
Ray.
Quiet!

10:55.781 --> 10:59.034
Stop it...
Quiet! Everybody, quiet!

11:09.628 --> 11:10.921
You're gonna miss your bus.

11:23.183 --> 11:25.769
How come they put "John"
on there, J. R?

11:25.978 --> 11:28.564
Your name's J.R., not John.

11:28.772 --> 11:32.401
Letters don't cut it in the Air Force,
Reba. They told me to pick a name.

11:34.194 --> 11:36.864
Communist troops
<i>have been driven out of Seoul...</i>

11:37.030 --> 11:39.741
<i>... by U.S. Forces,</i>
<i>led by General Douglas MacArth...</i>

11:41.285 --> 11:44.371
Oh. What's that?

11:46.540 --> 11:51.211
- Anybody seen Tommy? Hey.
- He's leaving, Ray. Come on.

11:53.797 --> 11:55.507
Now, don't start crying, Mama.

11:56.341 --> 11:59.928
- Be careful with that rifle, J.R.
- Yeah, I will, Mama.

12:00.053 --> 12:03.140
Last month that Purvis boy
got confused and shot himself.

12:03.348 --> 12:05.809
Ain't gonna be no battles, Carrie.

12:06.310 --> 12:08.812
He's going to Germany.
The war is in Korea.

12:09.479 --> 12:12.107
I love you.
- Love you too.

12:12.983 --> 12:14.568
Take this.

12:19.239 --> 12:21.033
Thanks, Mama.

12:21.742 --> 12:24.620
Take care of yourself, Donzil.
Take care of my sister too.

12:24.828 --> 12:26.538
I will.

12:26.830 --> 12:29.791
Hey, Tommy? Be a good boy.

12:34.630 --> 12:38.133
- You're gonna miss your bus.
- Yeah.

13:53.333 --> 13:56.253
Excuse me. May I?

14:49.389 --> 14:52.100
"Dear Vivian, I really miss you.

14:52.267 --> 14:54.561
Boo hoo hoo."

14:54.895 --> 14:56.772
It don't matter what you write, Cash.

14:56.980 --> 15:01.610
No chassis like that's gonna stay parked
in her daddy's driveway for two years.

15:18.252 --> 15:19.419
Cash.

15:19.962 --> 15:21.588
Write something.

15:42.150 --> 15:45.070
I saw this church in DÃ¼sseldorf
made of limestone.

15:45.279 --> 15:46.613
Big as a train station.

15:46.780 --> 15:49.074
We can get married there
and go to Venice.

15:49.283 --> 15:54.079
That's in Italy, Viv. The streets
are made of water. I ain't kidding.

15:54.204 --> 15:56.164
<i>Johnny...</i>

15:56.331 --> 15:58.750
<i>I haven't seen you for two years.</i>

15:59.668 --> 16:02.421
<i>We only dated for a month.</i>

16:02.963 --> 16:06.550
<i>My daddy says there's</i>
<i>something wrong with you.</i>

16:06.758 --> 16:10.179
Well, what do you say, Viv?

16:11.180 --> 16:14.349
<i>I mean, I thought you said</i>
<i>you loved me.</i>

16:14.558 --> 16:18.395
I do. Oh, I do. I...

16:19.021 --> 16:21.523
<i>Well, then don't be scared.</i>
<i>You tell him that.</i>

16:21.690 --> 16:25.110
<i>- You tell him I love you too.</i>
- He says that's impossible.

16:25.319 --> 16:29.198
- He says that you hardly know me.
- I think I know perfect when I meet it.

16:29.323 --> 16:31.200
Let's go, Cash.

16:32.618 --> 16:34.077
Viv...

16:34.411 --> 16:37.164
Listen, baby. You tell your daddy
I'm your man.

16:37.331 --> 16:40.834
Tell him we'll make a family, and I'm
gonna be on the radio because I am.

16:41.001 --> 16:43.754
You tell him we'll have a nice house,
and we'll be happy.

16:43.921 --> 16:46.548
We'll live in Memphis.
Tell him I'll love you forever.

16:46.673 --> 16:49.593
<i>- You promise?</i>
- That's a promise, Viv. You hear me...?

16:50.010 --> 16:53.055
Five minutes was up
five minutes ago.

17:00.562 --> 17:03.398
<i>I am Folsom Prison.</i>

17:03.524 --> 17:06.902
<i>At one time they called me</i>
<i>Bloody Folsom.</i>

17:07.444 --> 17:10.531
<i>And I earned the name.</i>
<i>My own prisoners built me.</i>

17:10.739 --> 17:15.202
<i>Every block of my granite</i>
<i>is cemented by the blood of men.</i>

17:15.410 --> 17:17.829
<i>Is it any wonder a man</i>
<i>sometimes went berserk...</i>

17:17.954 --> 17:20.499
<i>... and fought the hated walls</i>
<i>that shut him in?</i>

17:20.707 --> 17:23.210
<i>Knock it off, you.</i>
<i>Let a guy get some sleep.</i>

17:23.335 --> 17:26.421
<i>This was a common scene</i>
<i>in those old days.</i>

17:26.630 --> 17:29.091
<i>I had so little work for them to do.</i>

17:29.800 --> 17:33.178
<i>I hear the train comin'</i>

17:34.179 --> 17:37.099
<i>Comin' down the line</i>

17:38.350 --> 17:41.228
<i>I can't see no sunshine</i>

17:42.855 --> 17:46.984
<i>From this window of mine</i>

17:50.195 --> 17:51.530
I'm stuck.

17:51.738 --> 17:57.160
<i>When I was just a baby</i>
<i>My momma said to me, "Son"</i>

17:59.371 --> 18:01.874
<i>"Always be a good boy"</i>

18:03.125 --> 18:06.128
<i>"Don't you mess around with guns"</i>

18:07.629 --> 18:11.758
<i>But I killed a man in Reno</i>

18:15.095 --> 18:19.057
<i>Just to watch him die</i>

18:22.603 --> 18:26.148
<i>When I hear that whistle blowin'</i>

18:27.691 --> 18:30.110
<i>I hang my head...</i>

18:38.911 --> 18:41.371
<i>- and cry</i>

19:12.361 --> 19:14.780
You gonna try today, John?

19:15.280 --> 19:17.407
Really try to sell something?

19:17.533 --> 19:20.911
- What does that mean?
- I cleaned out your case last night.

19:21.745 --> 19:25.541
Baby, all I found were peanut bags
and music magazines.

19:27.251 --> 19:30.003
I need you to think
about what my daddy offered.

19:33.549 --> 19:37.261
Viv, I'm trying. I mean,
I'm really trying to sell stuff.

19:51.275 --> 19:54.653
Hello, ma'am. I'm from Home Equipment
Company over on Summer...

19:54.820 --> 19:57.155
...and we have a lot of products...

19:57.364 --> 20:01.869
Enamel colors that you can choose from,
uh, that we can...

20:02.035 --> 20:06.123
Hello, I'm John Cash, and I'm from the
Home Equipment Company on Summer.

20:06.290 --> 20:09.960
Lucretia. Lucretia, who is it?

20:50.542 --> 20:52.544
Hey, you are late.

21:27.871 --> 21:31.959
<i>Well, I woke up this morning</i>
<i>Looked out the door</i>

21:32.084 --> 21:35.462
<i>I can tell that old milk cow</i>
<i>By the way she lowed</i>

21:35.671 --> 21:40.759
<i>Well, if you've seen my milk cow</i>
<i>Please ride her on home</i>

21:42.970 --> 21:48.100
<i>I ain't had no milk and butter</i>
<i>Since that cow's been gone</i>

21:50.978 --> 21:54.273
<i>I've tried to treat you right</i>
<i>Day by day</i>

21:54.439 --> 21:57.734
<i>Get out your little prayer book</i>
<i>Get down on your knees and pray</i>

21:57.943 --> 22:00.070
<i>You're gonna need</i>

22:02.406 --> 22:05.242
<i>You're gonna need your lovin'</i>
<i>Daddy's help someday</i>

22:07.119 --> 22:12.749
<i>Well, then you're gonna be sorry</i>
<i>For treating me this way</i>

22:13.542 --> 22:15.085
Oh, come now!

22:28.390 --> 22:29.975
A little higher.

22:31.268 --> 22:33.645
You're close. Little higher.

22:35.355 --> 22:37.065
A little... Yeah, a little higher.

22:37.232 --> 22:39.443
Now play the chord.

22:42.529 --> 22:44.489
That's good.

22:45.199 --> 22:46.825
Let's hear your E, Marshall.

22:48.452 --> 22:50.204
There's my E.

22:51.371 --> 22:53.040
Loulabelle, time to come in.

22:54.458 --> 22:57.336
Jack. Jack, get in here.

22:57.669 --> 22:59.463
- Let's go.
Jack.

22:59.630 --> 23:01.590
Let's go, John.

23:06.678 --> 23:09.348
<i>There are some people</i>

23:10.849 --> 23:13.393
<i>Say you cannot tell</i>

23:14.978 --> 23:21.360
<i>Whether you are saved or</i>
<i>Whether all is well</i>

23:22.819 --> 23:25.489
<i>They say you only can hope and</i>

23:26.240 --> 23:29.618
<i>Trust that it is so</i>

23:30.869 --> 23:33.705
<i>Well, I was there when it happened</i>

23:33.872 --> 23:37.501
<i>And so I guess I ought to know</i>

23:39.044 --> 23:41.672
<i>Yes, I know when Jesus saved me</i>

23:41.880 --> 23:45.551
<i>- Saved my soul</i>
<i>- The very moment He forgave me</i>

23:45.759 --> 23:47.511
<i>Made me whole</i>

23:47.719 --> 23:49.930
<i>He took away my heavy burdens</i>

23:50.138 --> 23:53.392
<i>Lord, He gave me peace within</i>

23:53.934 --> 23:58.188
<i>- Peace within</i>
<i>- Well, Satan can't make me doubt it</i>

23:58.313 --> 23:59.940
<i>I won't doubt it</i>

24:02.526 --> 24:03.861
<i>I'm gonna shout it...</i>

24:04.069 --> 24:05.153
Viv?

24:13.412 --> 24:14.955
Viv, open the door.

24:15.581 --> 24:17.040
Viv.

24:20.752 --> 24:24.381
Viv, don't embarrass me.
Everyone's out there watching.

24:30.304 --> 24:32.764
I wanna see my daddy.

24:33.473 --> 24:37.436
I wanna go home, John. Please.

24:37.603 --> 24:40.856
He's just got a job sitting in there,
in San Antonio waiting for us.

24:41.023 --> 24:43.901
- It's just sitting there, waiting.
- Viv. The guys are here.

24:44.026 --> 24:46.069
My band is here in Memphis.

24:46.612 --> 24:49.740
Your band? John, your band?

24:49.865 --> 24:54.620
Your band is two mechanics
who can't hardly play.

24:55.454 --> 24:59.333
Oh, baby, can't you hear the difference
between you and that?

24:59.499 --> 25:04.046
You have your wife and your baby
in a dump, John...

25:04.213 --> 25:09.635
...and another one on the way.
And we can't even make rent.

25:09.801 --> 25:11.345
John...

25:21.688 --> 25:27.194
<i>Soon your sugar-daddies will all be gone</i>

25:28.278 --> 25:33.700
<i>You'll wake up some cold day</i>
<i>And find you're alone</i>

25:34.284 --> 25:40.791
<i>You'll call for me</i>
<i>But I'm gonna tell you, "Bye, bye, bye"</i>

25:40.916 --> 25:47.214
<i>When I turn around and walk away</i>
<i>You'll cry, cry, cry</i>

25:48.590 --> 25:52.135
<i>You're gonna cry, cry, cry</i>

25:52.302 --> 25:55.806
<i>And you'll cry alone</i>

25:55.973 --> 26:01.603
<i>When everyone's forgotten</i>
<i>And you're left on your own</i>

26:01.770 --> 26:07.693
<i>You're gonna cry, cry, cry</i>

26:09.778 --> 26:11.280
Hey.

26:11.822 --> 26:14.658
- You hate me?
- No, I don't.

26:16.118 --> 26:17.369
That's a mean song.

26:18.453 --> 26:20.080
Stupid is what it is, Viv.

26:21.748 --> 26:23.125
Yeah.

26:28.130 --> 26:31.133
Vi... Viv, it's just a song.

26:48.734 --> 26:51.403
Excuse me, sir?
You the owner of this place?

26:51.570 --> 26:54.448
- That's me.
- Hello. I'm J.R. Cash.

26:54.573 --> 26:55.949
Sam Phillips.

26:56.074 --> 26:59.119
Good to meet you, Mr. Phillips.
I'm a singer, and I got a band.

26:59.244 --> 27:00.829
We've been working on some songs.

27:00.996 --> 27:03.040
You wanna cut a record, son,
it's $4.

27:03.248 --> 27:06.460
Well, what about the guys there
on the wall in the pictures?

27:06.585 --> 27:09.671
- I mean, they pay $4?
- They're on my label.

27:09.880 --> 27:11.715
Well, how do I get on there?

27:11.882 --> 27:14.009
- You audition.
- Right now?

27:14.134 --> 27:16.011
No...

27:16.220 --> 27:18.430
Call my secretary, Marion,
when she comes back.

27:18.555 --> 27:21.475
She's at the salon. She'll get you
an appointment next month.

27:21.642 --> 27:25.020
- I can't wait that long, Mr. Phillips.
- Excuse me?

27:26.188 --> 27:27.940
I can't wait that long.

27:31.193 --> 27:34.321
- What about this one? I can iron it.
- No.

27:34.530 --> 27:37.241
John, you can't wear that one.
It's black.

27:37.449 --> 27:40.661
It's the only color of shirt we all have.
Nothing wrong with black.

27:40.786 --> 27:44.331
- It looks like you're going to a funeral.
- Well, maybe I am.

27:45.082 --> 27:48.961
<i>Yes, I know when Jesus saved me</i>
Saved my soul

27:49.169 --> 27:52.965
<i>The very moment He forgave me</i>
<i>- Made me whole</i>

27:53.131 --> 27:59.680
<i>He took away my heavy burdens</i>
<i>Lord, He gave me peace within</i>

27:59.930 --> 28:03.892
<i>- Peace within</i>
<i>- Well, Satan can't make me doubt it</i>

28:04.101 --> 28:07.521
I won't doubt it
<i>- It's real and I'm gonna shout it</i>

28:07.729 --> 28:09.439
<i>I'm gonna shout it</i>

28:09.648 --> 28:11.525
Hold on. Hold on.

28:11.692 --> 28:15.028
I hate to interrupt,
but you guys got something else?

28:19.199 --> 28:22.953
I'm sorry. I can't market gospel
no more.

28:26.164 --> 28:27.875
So that's it?

28:29.459 --> 28:32.754
I don't record material
that doesn't sell, Mr. Cash.

28:32.921 --> 28:35.591
And gospel like that doesn't sell.

28:36.633 --> 28:38.969
So is it the gospel
or the way I sing it?

28:39.303 --> 28:40.971
Both.

28:41.388 --> 28:43.974
Well, what's wrong
with the way I sing it?

28:44.141 --> 28:45.601
I don't believe you.

28:46.852 --> 28:51.106
- You saying I don't believe in God?
J.R., come on. Let's go.

28:51.315 --> 28:54.359
No. I wanna understand.
I mean, we come down here...

28:54.568 --> 28:56.945
...we play, and he tells me
I don't believe in God.

28:57.112 --> 29:01.992
You know exactly what I'm telling you.
We've already heard that song.

29:02.659 --> 29:07.915
A hundred times. Just like that.
Just like how you singing it.

29:08.790 --> 29:12.044
- Well, you didn't let us bring it home.
- Bring it...

29:12.211 --> 29:16.590
Bring it home?
All right, let's bring it home.

29:17.591 --> 29:21.136
If you was hit by a truck, and you
was lying out in that gutter dying...

29:21.303 --> 29:24.515
...and you had time to sing
one song, huh?

29:24.681 --> 29:28.352
One song people would remember
before you're dirt...

29:28.560 --> 29:32.940
...one song that would let God know
what you felt about your time...

29:33.148 --> 29:36.235
...here on Earth, one song
that would sum you up...

29:36.401 --> 29:38.904
...you telling me
that's the song you'd sing?

29:39.071 --> 29:43.659
That same Jimmie Davis tune
we hear on the radio all day?

29:44.243 --> 29:47.079
About your peace within
and how it's real...

29:47.204 --> 29:49.790
...and how you're gonna shout it?

29:49.998 --> 29:53.168
Or would you sing
something different?

29:53.293 --> 29:55.504
Something real? Something you felt?

29:55.671 --> 29:58.173
I'm telling you right now,
that's the kind of song...

29:58.340 --> 30:00.801
...people want to hear.
That's the kind of song...

30:00.926 --> 30:03.512
...that truly saves people.

30:04.429 --> 30:07.850
It ain't got nothing to do
with believing in God, Mr. Cash.

30:08.058 --> 30:10.769
It has to do with believing in yourself.

30:16.608 --> 30:19.695
Well, I got a couple songs
I wrote in the Air Force.

30:22.281 --> 30:24.658
You got anything
against the Air Force?

30:25.492 --> 30:26.952
No.

30:28.704 --> 30:30.581
I do.

30:33.750 --> 30:36.962
J.R., whatever you're about
to play, we ain't never heard it.

30:40.090 --> 30:43.385
<i>I hear the train a-comin'</i>

30:44.261 --> 30:47.639
<i>It's rollin' around the bend</i>

30:48.348 --> 30:52.019
<i>And I ain't seen the sunshine</i>

30:52.352 --> 30:55.480
<i>Since I don't know when</i>

30:56.315 --> 31:00.402
<i>I'm stuck in Folsom Prison</i>

31:01.528 --> 31:06.033
<i>And time keeps draggin' on</i>

31:12.039 --> 31:16.460
<i>But that train keeps a-rollin'</i>

31:17.461 --> 31:22.090
<i>On down to San Antone</i>

31:24.134 --> 31:27.304
<i>When I was just a baby</i>

31:27.804 --> 31:31.099
<i>My momma told me, "Son"</i>

31:31.850 --> 31:37.940
<i>"Always be a good boy</i>
<i>Don't ever play with guns"</i>

31:38.065 --> 31:41.944
<i>But I shot a man in Reno</i>

31:42.819 --> 31:46.740
<i>Just to watch him die</i>

31:50.744 --> 31:54.081
<i>When I hear that whistle blowin'</i>

31:54.748 --> 31:58.544
<i>I hang my head and cry</i>

31:59.670 --> 32:04.925
<i>I bet there's rich folks eatin'</i>
<i>In a fancy dining car</i>

32:05.092 --> 32:10.013
<i>They're probably drinkin' coffee</i>
<i>And smokin' big cigars</i>

32:10.180 --> 32:13.141
<i>Well, I know I had it comin'</i>

32:13.851 --> 32:17.354
<i>I know I can't be free</i>

32:20.691 --> 32:23.735
<i>But those people keep a-movin'</i>

32:24.319 --> 32:28.031
<i>And that's what tortures me</i>

33:01.231 --> 33:03.025
Where you been?

33:04.359 --> 33:05.986
Are you drunk?

33:09.573 --> 33:13.660
- What happened?
- He didn't like our gospel.

33:15.078 --> 33:17.456
So I played him some songs
that I wrote.

33:18.790 --> 33:21.210
And we made a record, Viv.

33:21.376 --> 33:23.754
I mean a real, real record.

33:28.300 --> 33:32.596
We did it like six times. I had to sing
the song over and over again.

33:32.763 --> 33:36.266
And I'm playing it, and you should've
seen Marshall, he was so nervous.

33:36.433 --> 33:38.810
But, I mean, we made
a real record of my song.

33:38.936 --> 33:41.730
- Oh, gee.
- I can't believe it. It's still...

33:46.985 --> 33:50.155
Yes, sirree, you're listening
<i>to the Tennessee Farm Hour.</i>

33:50.322 --> 33:53.700
Now, here's a new one
from our girl Patsy.

34:05.629 --> 34:06.922
Good lyrics.

34:07.256 --> 34:08.632
Did you write it?

34:08.841 --> 34:11.260
Yeah, it won a poetry prize
<i>in Stars and Stripes.</i>

34:11.510 --> 34:14.429
That was before...
That was before I set it to music.

34:22.563 --> 34:24.356
Hey, flip that over for me, will you?

34:28.360 --> 34:32.155
This is Bob Neal, and you're listening
<i>to the Tennessee Farm Hour...</i>

34:32.364 --> 34:34.449
...brought to you
by Bronson Seed and Feed.

34:36.409 --> 34:39.621
Mr. Phillips? Oh, man, I broke it.
I broke it, I broke it.

34:39.830 --> 34:42.833
John. John. Broke what?
- The record, man, it's smashed.

34:43.000 --> 34:44.710
Mr. Neal, he asked me to flip it over...

34:44.835 --> 34:47.963
...and when I went to do it,
it slipped out of my hands and it broke.

34:48.130 --> 34:50.549
The worst part is, I think he liked it.

34:50.716 --> 34:52.885
John, I know.
We can do it right now.

34:53.051 --> 34:55.929
- Let's get Luther and Marshall.
- We don't need to record it. Sit down.

34:56.054 --> 34:57.222
- I wanna record it.
- John.

34:57.431 --> 35:01.143
Sit down, John.
You don't have to record another one.

35:01.310 --> 35:02.936
What you broke is the test press.

35:03.103 --> 35:07.482
The factory sends me one of those
before they do a run of a thousand.

35:09.484 --> 35:11.862
He's yanking your chain, Mr. Phillips.

35:12.070 --> 35:13.864
Ain't no way nobody
could be that dumb.

35:14.031 --> 35:15.490
Leave him be, Jerry Lee.

35:24.499 --> 35:26.960
John?
Hmm?

35:28.212 --> 35:30.672
When are we gonna talk about...

35:30.839 --> 35:33.592
...how this tour is gonna work?

35:34.301 --> 35:36.011
Because you're...

35:36.220 --> 35:41.350
...out of town three out of four weeks
for the next three months.

35:42.559 --> 35:44.144
Well...

35:46.271 --> 35:48.565
You wanted it.
- Viv, I don't believe it.

35:48.732 --> 35:50.275
He's playing it again.

35:50.442 --> 35:52.069
<i>Them folks at Sun tell me...</i>

35:52.194 --> 35:54.780
<i>... this boy starts a
<i>four-state tour next week.</i></i>

35:58.659 --> 36:00.744
Ho-ho! Son of a gun!

36:00.911 --> 36:03.580
We got a baby sleeping. Come on.

36:10.045 --> 36:12.005
Vivian, you hear that?

36:13.006 --> 36:15.509
Hey! Hey, that's my song!

36:15.634 --> 36:17.052
Oh, the baby.

36:29.273 --> 36:31.191
Hear Daddy in the wind?

36:34.862 --> 36:37.281
<i>Cry, cry, cry</i>

36:37.489 --> 36:39.575
I think she really likes it.

36:53.589 --> 36:56.383
<i>My name is Jerry Lee Lewis</i>
<i>Come from Louisiana</i>

36:56.550 --> 36:59.094
<i>Gonna do a little boogie</i>
<i>On this here piano!</i>

36:59.261 --> 37:01.972
<i>Doing mighty fine</i>
<i>Gonna make you shake it</i>

37:02.181 --> 37:04.850
<i>Gonna make you do it</i>
<i>Make you do it till it breaks</i>

37:05.058 --> 37:07.436
<i>Called the Lewis Boogie</i>
<i>In the Lewis way</i>

37:07.603 --> 37:11.690
<i>Lord, I do my little boogie-woogie</i>
<i>Every day</i>

37:16.320 --> 37:19.031
Never seen nobody play like that.

37:26.455 --> 37:29.249
<i>Well, down in New Orleans</i>

37:29.374 --> 37:32.044
<i>The land of dreams</i>
<i>The best doggone place, son</i>

37:32.211 --> 37:34.630
<i>You ever have seen</i>
<i>Yeah, the cats go wild</i>

37:34.796 --> 37:37.841
<i>With a boogie that's hot</i>
<i>And my boogie makes you want to stop</i>

37:38.050 --> 37:40.093
<i>And do the bop</i>
<i>It's called the Lewis Boogie</i>

37:40.302 --> 37:42.012
<i>In the Lewis way</i>

37:42.221 --> 37:47.601
<i>I do my little boogie-woogie</i>
<i>Every day!</i>

37:49.520 --> 37:54.775
Jerry Lee Lewis, ladies and
gentlemen. "The Killer," Jerry Lee Lewis.

37:56.109 --> 37:58.570
Grab yourselves a pine box, boys.

37:58.695 --> 38:00.781
Nobody follows "The Killer."

38:00.989 --> 38:05.285
These next boys have just put out
their first record called "Cry, Cry, Cry."

38:05.452 --> 38:07.829
Oh, shoot. Now I'm late.

38:07.955 --> 38:10.082
Oh, my gosh. Excuse me.

38:10.290 --> 38:14.002
That's my cue. Oh, no, y...
Oh, that's stuck right on my dress.

38:14.211 --> 38:18.382
- Hey, Bill. Hold on, Bill. I'm coming.
- I think...

38:18.590 --> 38:22.219
Oh, my, I think I hear June Carter's
voice, ladies and gentlemen.

38:24.513 --> 38:27.224
I'll be right there, Bill.
I'll be right there.

38:27.432 --> 38:29.434
Reckon when, June?

38:29.977 --> 38:32.896
Well, Bill, I got tangled.

38:33.522 --> 38:37.860
- In what, June bug?
Johnny Cash's guitar strap.

38:39.111 --> 38:42.155
Don't worry, I can keep this funny
for at least two minutes.

38:42.322 --> 38:45.701
And I'll tell you what, Bill.
He's a strapping boy, that Johnny Cash.

38:45.909 --> 38:49.121
And his guitar strap's
pretty strapping too.

38:50.330 --> 38:53.250
Here. I love that "Cry" song,
by the way.

38:53.709 --> 38:55.210
Hey, thanks.

38:55.419 --> 38:57.212
Ladies and gentlemen,
Miss June Carter.

38:57.421 --> 39:01.592
Bill. Bill, I had to come and tell you.
I had to tell you.

39:01.800 --> 39:05.721
I had to tell you.
I just can't sing tonight.

39:07.723 --> 39:09.349
You best be getting out here.

39:09.850 --> 39:10.893
Yeah.

39:11.059 --> 39:13.854
Bill, I got the laryngitis.

39:14.354 --> 39:15.439
Me too.

39:15.564 --> 39:18.025
June, we just...
- I do. Y'all laughing, but I do.

39:19.443 --> 39:22.404
We all just heard you hollering
up a storm backstage.

39:23.530 --> 39:26.241
Well, I didn't have it then, Bill.

39:28.744 --> 39:31.079
Ladies and gentlemen,
Miss June Carter.

39:39.463 --> 39:41.632
All right, June's gonna be back
to sing later.

39:41.840 --> 39:43.634
Her family's also with us tonight.

39:43.800 --> 39:47.804
But like I was saying, these boys
up next are hotter than a pistol.

39:47.971 --> 39:51.600
They are burning up the radio
with their new hit, "Cry, Cry, Cry."

39:51.725 --> 39:54.645
And I wanna make sure we give them
a big Texarkana welcome.

39:54.811 --> 39:58.232
So here they are, folks. New passengers
on the Sun Rocking Railway...

39:58.440 --> 40:00.901
...Johnny Cash
and the Tennessee Two.

40:13.705 --> 40:17.251
Hello. I'm Johnny Cash.

40:27.511 --> 40:32.140
<i>Hey, get rhythm</i>
<i>When you get the blues</i>

40:32.266 --> 40:36.603
<i>Come on, get rhythm</i>
<i>When you get the blues</i>

40:37.229 --> 40:39.189
<i>Get a rock 'n' roll feelin'</i>
<i>In your bones</i>

40:39.356 --> 40:41.567
<i>Get taps on your toes</i>
<i>And get gone</i>

40:41.733 --> 40:45.654
<i>Get rhythm when you get the blues</i>

40:47.030 --> 40:49.700
<i>Little shoeshine boy</i>
<i>Never gets low down</i>

40:49.867 --> 40:51.577
<i>But he's got the dirtiest</i>
<i>Job in town</i>

40:51.743 --> 40:55.873
<i>Bendin' low at the people's feet</i>
<i>On the windy corner of a dirty street</i>

40:56.039 --> 40:58.041
<i>Well, I asked him</i>
<i>While he shined my shoes</i>

40:58.250 --> 41:00.210
<i>How he'd keep</i>
<i>From getting the blues</i>

41:00.419 --> 41:02.212
<i>He grinned as he raised his little head</i>

41:02.421 --> 41:04.381
<i>He popped a shoeshine rag</i>
<i>And then he said</i>

41:04.590 --> 41:08.594
<i>"Get rhythm when you get the blues</i>

41:08.760 --> 41:13.557
<i>Come on, get rhythm</i>
<i>When you get the blues</i>

41:13.724 --> 41:15.726
<i>Yes, a jumpy rhythm</i>
<i>Makes you feel so fine</i>

41:15.893 --> 41:18.520
<i>It'll shake all the trouble</i>
<i>From your worried mind</i>

41:18.645 --> 41:22.316
<i>Get rhythm when you get the blues"</i>

41:39.249 --> 41:40.751
All right.

41:41.960 --> 41:44.213
<i>Well, I sat down to listen</i>
<i>To the shoeshine boy</i>

41:44.379 --> 41:46.590
<i>And I thought I was gonna jump for joy</i>

41:46.715 --> 41:48.634
<i>Slapped on the shoe polish</i>
<i>Left and right</i>

41:48.800 --> 41:50.969
<i>He took a shoeshine rag</i>
<i>And he held it tight</i>

41:51.136 --> 41:52.930
<i>He stopped once</i>
<i>To wipe the sweat away</i>

41:53.096 --> 41:55.641
<i>I said, "You're a mighty little boy</i>
<i>To be a-workin' thataway"</i>

41:55.766 --> 41:57.351
<i>He said, "I like it"</i>
<i>With a big, wide grin</i>

41:57.559 --> 41:59.269
<i>Kept on a-poppin' and he said again</i>

41:59.436 --> 42:03.190
<i>"Get rhythm when you get the blues</i>

42:03.357 --> 42:04.566
<i>Come on and get rhythm</i>

42:04.733 --> 42:05.901
All right!

42:06.109 --> 42:08.237
<i>When you get the blues</i>

42:08.445 --> 42:10.781
<i>It only costs a dime, just a nickel a shoe</i>

42:10.989 --> 42:13.075
<i>It does a million dollars' worth</i>
<i>Of good for you</i>

42:13.242 --> 42:18.580
<i>Get rhythm when you get the blues"</i>

42:24.169 --> 42:27.840
Thank you. Thank you very much.

42:28.173 --> 42:29.925
<i>Well, I love that hair, long and black</i>

42:30.092 --> 42:32.010
<i>Hanging down to the middle of your back</i>

42:32.135 --> 42:35.806
<i>Don't cut it off, whatever you do</i>
<i>I need it to run my fingers through</i>

42:36.014 --> 42:39.393
Viv, I'm telling you, I think this is
the best show we've ever done.

42:39.560 --> 42:42.646
Hell, it might be the best show
I've ever seen, no kidding.

42:42.813 --> 42:46.441
<i>Where are you?</i>
- Texarkana. Baby, I miss you.

42:46.650 --> 42:50.362
Hey, do you hear Orbison doing our
song? He turned it to a two-step. Listen.

43:06.670 --> 43:07.796
- Do you hear that?
<i>- Damn it.</i>

43:07.963 --> 43:09.006
What's the matter?

43:10.424 --> 43:12.509
<i>Damn it. Roseanne just ran</i>
<i>her head into the table.</i>

43:12.676 --> 43:15.929
<i>Roseanne.</i>
<i>Roseanne. Here, talk to Daddy.</i>

43:16.096 --> 43:18.515
Hey, Roseanne? Hey, it's Daddy.

43:18.682 --> 43:22.519
Honey, don't, don't cry.
Daddy's gonna be home real soon.

43:22.686 --> 43:24.229
<i>- John, I have to go.</i>
- Huh?

43:24.479 --> 43:26.231
<i>I have to go, John.</i>

43:27.441 --> 43:28.859
Bye.

43:35.365 --> 43:38.785
Hey, y'all say hi to Johnny Cash.
Dad, he wrote that "Cry, Cry, Cry" song.

43:38.994 --> 43:40.204
Mother Maybelle.

43:40.370 --> 43:43.415
- How you doing, Johnny Cash?
- Good. Heck, I'm great, ma'am.

43:43.624 --> 43:45.709
- Hello, John, I'm Ezra.
- Yeah, I know.

43:46.585 --> 43:50.005
- It was nice to meet you, son.
- Real good to meet you, sir.

44:12.611 --> 44:16.406
<i>I walked into a honky-tonky</i>
<i>Just the other day</i>

44:16.573 --> 44:20.285
<i>I dropped a nickel in a jukebox</i>
<i>Just to hear it play</i>

44:20.494 --> 44:24.331
<i>I didn't have no tune in mind</i>
<i>I didn't wait to choose</i>

44:24.831 --> 44:28.961
<i>Just dropped a nickel in the slot</i>
<i>And played the Jukebox Blues</i>

44:36.552 --> 44:38.512
<i>There's a guy in there</i>
<i>With an old tin horn</i>

44:38.720 --> 44:40.514
<i>And a feller on an old banjo</i>

44:40.681 --> 44:42.766
<i>And the man on the fiddle</i>
<i>He wasn't no slouch</i>

44:42.933 --> 44:45.102
<i>He could really drag that bow</i>

44:48.230 --> 44:51.233
You sounded good tonight, Cash.
Real tight.

44:51.400 --> 44:53.652
Oh, thanks, man.

44:54.570 --> 44:56.321
You want some chili fries?

44:56.530 --> 44:58.740
Oh, no, that's okay.

44:58.949 --> 45:02.911
She's been in the spotlight since
you and me was biting ankles.

45:03.287 --> 45:05.372
They say Maybelle
had a crib at the Ryman...

45:05.581 --> 45:08.375
...so she could pull her out
and let her whoop and holler...

45:08.542 --> 45:10.711
...and pop her back in
and go to sleep.

45:10.836 --> 45:12.379
<i>It must have been a drum</i>

45:12.796 --> 45:16.884
<i>It gave that song a solid beat</i>
<i>Boy, he was goin' some</i>

45:24.516 --> 45:28.395
<i>I walked into a honky-tonky</i>
<i>Just the other day</i>

45:28.604 --> 45:32.232
<i>I dropped a nickel in a jukebox</i>
<i>Just to hear it play</i>

45:32.649 --> 45:36.570
<i>I didn't have no tune in mind</i>
<i>I didn't wait to choose</i>

45:36.737 --> 45:40.574
<i>Just dropped a nickel in the slot</i>
<i>And played the Jukebox Blues</i>

45:48.665 --> 45:52.461
<i>I've played a lot of jukeboxes</i>
<i>Most every one in town</i>

45:52.669 --> 45:56.965
<i>But that's the first tune I ever heard</i>
<i>That could make one dance around</i>

45:58.926 --> 46:00.761
<i>Play the Jukebox Blues</i>

46:00.969 --> 46:04.890
<i>Such a rhythm I never heard</i>
<i>I danced out both of my shoes</i>

46:16.151 --> 46:19.196
- We're leaving in an hour, John.
All right.

46:21.240 --> 46:24.284
Oh, that's a sweet story, honey.

46:25.035 --> 46:26.745
All right.

46:26.954 --> 46:28.497
No.

46:29.665 --> 46:31.333
I'm leaving in, like, five minutes.

46:32.292 --> 46:33.710
All right.

46:33.836 --> 46:36.129
Is everything else all right?

46:37.631 --> 46:39.174
I love you too.

46:40.926 --> 46:43.595
- Bye-bye. Bye-bye.
How you doing?

46:43.762 --> 46:45.556
- Coffee?
- Yeah...

46:45.764 --> 46:47.599
...and some toast, please.

46:51.645 --> 46:53.313
- Hey.
- Hey, how are you?

46:53.480 --> 46:54.815
Good. Do you mind?

46:54.982 --> 46:56.483
No, not at all.

46:56.650 --> 46:59.111
- Did you lose your voice?
- I did.

46:59.236 --> 47:01.154
I was just singing my heart out
up there.

47:01.572 --> 47:05.242
I got to ask you how you came up
with that sound.

47:05.492 --> 47:06.535
What sound?

47:06.702 --> 47:10.706
That sound everybody's talking about.
Steady like a train. Sharp like a razor.

47:11.957 --> 47:15.210
Well, we'd play faster if we could.

47:15.377 --> 47:18.797
You know, I guess
it just come out like that.

47:19.590 --> 47:22.384
I gotta close my register.
- Oh, yeah, sure.

47:24.595 --> 47:26.430
Thank you.

47:28.223 --> 47:30.934
Here's a picture of my wife, Viv.

47:31.143 --> 47:34.605
- My baby, Roseanne.
- Oh, look at her. She's beautiful.

47:35.355 --> 47:37.065
Thanks. Got another one on the way.

47:37.232 --> 47:38.734
- I got a little girl too.
- Yeah?

47:38.901 --> 47:41.820
Her name's Carlene. Yeah.
She's about the same age.

47:45.782 --> 47:48.911
When I was in the service,
I used to look at pictures of you.

47:49.036 --> 47:51.205
- You know, in magazines.
- Oh.

47:53.457 --> 47:55.959
No. No, it wasn't like that.

47:56.126 --> 47:58.420
I mean, I...
I liked your music, you know?

47:58.587 --> 48:00.214
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

48:00.380 --> 48:04.384
I mean, I... You were... Well, you are...
I mean, I... I kept track of you.

48:04.593 --> 48:06.887
Yeah, you and your family, you know.

48:07.054 --> 48:09.640
I listened to your voice my whole life,
you know?

48:10.933 --> 48:14.937
Now, me and my brother, Jack,
we always listened to your songs.

48:15.103 --> 48:17.105
- You know, like "Swallerin' Place."
- Yeah.

48:17.272 --> 48:20.526
Yeah, we liked it
when you'd sing one alone.

48:20.692 --> 48:23.612
Well, you and Jack are the only ones.

48:24.530 --> 48:28.283
- What do you mean?
- I'm not really much of a singer, John.

48:28.450 --> 48:32.287
I mean, I got a lot of personality,
I got sass.

48:32.454 --> 48:36.500
I give it my all, but my sister Anita's
really the one who's got the pipes.

48:36.792 --> 48:38.544
- Well, who said that?
- Everybody.

48:38.710 --> 48:40.420
My mama, my daddy.

48:40.587 --> 48:44.800
That's how come I learned to be funny.
So I'd have something to offer.

48:47.010 --> 48:48.971
Well...

48:49.263 --> 48:51.640
Parents aren't always
the best judge of things...

48:51.765 --> 48:53.517
...you want my opinion.

48:57.563 --> 48:59.982
So how long you on the tour?

49:00.190 --> 49:03.151
Another couple of weeks.
We just got on board...

49:03.360 --> 49:06.697
...but I tell you,
it feels like a lot longer.

49:06.864 --> 49:08.365
I'm sure.

49:08.574 --> 49:10.492
I'm headed off.
I'm going to the Ryman.

49:10.701 --> 49:13.495
Tell your brother Jack to tune in,
I'll sing him something.

49:13.662 --> 49:14.997
What does he like?

49:15.163 --> 49:19.459
Oh, that's... That's sweet.
But he passed.

49:19.626 --> 49:22.754
I'm sorry. Were y'all real close?

49:23.380 --> 49:27.676
Yeah. Yeah, he's, uh...

49:31.346 --> 49:36.185
It's funny, I ain't talked about Jack
in a long time, you know? It's...

49:37.686 --> 49:42.191
After he died, I...
I talked about him all the time...

49:44.193 --> 49:47.196
...but I guess people grew tired of it.

